org.jamesframework.core.problems.solutions

Class Solution

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jamesframework.core.problems.solutions.Solution
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SubsetSolution

    public abstract class Solution
extends Object
    Represents an abstract solution. Every solution class should provide methods to compute the hash code of a specific solution, and to check for conceptual equality with other solutions. The implemented equality should be consistent with the computed hash codes, i.e. two solutions which are deemed equal should produce the same hash code, while unequal solutions may (and preferably should) produce different hash codes.
    Author:
    Herman De Beukelaer

      • isSameSolution

        public abstract boolean isSameSolution(Solution sol)
        Checks whether this solution is conceptually equal to an other, given solution. The implementation should be consistent with computeHashCode(), i.e. if it returns true, both solutions should always yield the same hash code.
        Parameters:
        sol - other solution to check for equality
        Returns:
        true if both solutions are conceptually equal

      • computeHashCode

        public abstract int computeHashCode()
        Compute a hash code for this solution. The implementation should be consistent with isSameSolution(Solution), i.e. it should return exactly the same hash code for any solution which is deemed equal.
        Returns:
        computed hash code
